 have happened. Silly perhaps, but at least clear. The gift of penetrating life’s devices, an innate disposition toward the constant exercise of the creative faculty could alone have enabled me … At this point I should have compared the breaker of the law which makes such a fuss over a little spilled blood, with a poet or a stage performer. But as my poor left-handed friend used to put it: philosophic speculation is the invention of the rich. Down with it.

